            <short>Bypass delay when the new active window is the focused window.</short>

      <value>
        <schema>
          <type>bool</type>
          <locale name="C">
            <default_value>
              <value>
                <bool>true</bool>
              </value>
            </default_value>
            <short>Framebuffer object</short>
            <long>Render all frames indirectly using framebuffer objects (GL_EXT_framebuffer_object), if supported by the driver. Pros: Might be faster than the default buffer swapping method in some cases. Cons: This will come at the cost of (1) usually reduced graphics benchmark performance; (2) increased GPU resource consumption; and (3) possibly higher visible lag. Note: This feature is always on in OpenGL|ES builds such as ARM platforms.</long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>

            <short>Keyboard shortcut to make font larger</short>

          will be no keyboard shortcut for this action.

      <value>
        <schema>
          <type>string</type>
          <locale name="C">
            <default_value>
              <value>
                <string>ascii-del</string>
              </value>
            </default_value>
            <short>Effect of the Backspace key</short>
            <long>
          Sets what code the backspace key generates. Possible values 
          are &quot;ascii-del&quot; for the ASCII DEL character, 
          &quot;control-h&quot; for Control-H (AKA the ASCII BS character), 
          &quot;escape-sequence&quot; for the escape sequence typically 
          bound to backspace or delete. &quot;ascii-del&quot; is normally 
          considered the correct setting for the Backspace key.
         </long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>
    </entry>

              </value>

            <long>
           Number of scrollback lines to keep around. You can
           scroll back in the terminal by this number of lines;
           lines that don&apos;t fit in the scrollback are discarded.
   If scrollback_unlimited is true, this value is ignored.
         </long>

    <entry>
      <key>/schemas/apps/gnome-terminal/profiles/Default/scrollback_unlimited</key>
      <value>
        <schema>
          <type>bool</type>
          <locale name="C">
            <default_value>
              <value>
                <bool>false</bool>
              </value>
            </default_value>
            <short>Whether an unlimited number of lines should be kept in scrollback</short>
            <long>
   If true, scrollback lines will never be discarded.  The scrollback
   history is stored on disk temporarily, so this may cause the system
   to run out of disk space if there is a lot of output to the
   terminal.
         </long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>

            <long>Maximum size of the thumbnail cache, in megabytes. Set to -1 to disable cleaning.</long>
          </locale>

    <entry>
      <key>/schemas/system/http_proxy/ignore_hosts</key>
      <value>
        <schema>
          <type>list</type>
          <list_type>string</list_type>
          <locale name="C">
            <default_value>
              <value>
                <list type="string">
                    <value>
                      <string>localhost</string>
                    </value>
                    <value>
                      <string>127.0.0.0/8</string>
                    </value>
                    <value>
                      <string>*.local</string>
                    </value>
                </list>
              </value>
            </default_value>
            <short>Non-proxy hosts</short>
            <long>This key contains a list of hosts which are connected to
directly, rather than via the proxy (if it is active). The values can
be hostnames, domains (using an initial wildcard like *.foo.com), IP
host addresses (both IPv4 and IPv6) and network addresses with a
netmask (something like 192.168.0.0/24).</long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>
    </entry>
    <entry>

              <value>
                <int>8080</int>
              </value>
            </default_value>

            <long>The port on the machine defined by &quot;/system/http_proxy/host&quot;
        that you proxy through.</long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <key>/schemas/system/http_proxy/use_authentication</key>
      <value>
        <schema>
          <type>bool</type>
          <locale name="C">
            <default_value>
              <value>
                <bool>false</bool>
              </value>
            </default_value>
            <short>Authenticate proxy server connections</short>
            <long>If true, then connections to the proxy server require
        authentication. The username/password combo is defined by
        &quot;/system/http_proxy/authentication_user&quot; and
        &quot;/system/http_proxy/authentication_password&quot;.</long>
          </locale>
        </schema>
      </value>
    </entry>
